1
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:37,100
<i> I will make it up to you.</i>

2
00:00:37,233 --> 00:00:38,667
<i> I will make Coleen pay.</i>

3
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:39,967
<i> You have no shame.</i>

4
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:42,133
<i>You're the reason why
Jessica is dead!</i>

5
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,367
<i> Stop accusing my daughter!</i>

6
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:46,633
<i>And stop defending
your lying daughter!</i>

7
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>Someone who saw us could
think I pushed her.</i>

8
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,233
<i> What do you mean?</i>

9
00:00:51,367 --> 00:00:56,367
<i>We were struggling until
I accidentally let go, Mom.</i>

10
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,100
<i>I'll make that damned
killer answer for what he did!</i>

11
00:00:59,233 --> 00:01:01,133
<i>The driver is the one
who ran over my child.</i>

12
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:04,267
<i> But Coleen killed Jessica.</i>

13
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:08,167
<i>I'll make sure that
woman rots in jail.</i>

14
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:17,567
Manuel.

15
00:01:19,867 --> 00:01:21,467
I don't know what to do, Felma.

16
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,600
<i> I'm cornered.</i>

17
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,833
I'm grieving one child,

18
00:01:31,967 --> 00:01:35,000
and the other is being accused
of killing her.

19
00:01:39,967 --> 00:01:40,867
Manuel,

20
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:46,533
I'm just trying
to understand Hazel.

21
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:50,600
She's grieving.

22
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,033
She's angry.

23
00:01:54,967 --> 00:01:58,433
That's why she's looking
for someone to blame.

24
00:01:59,167 --> 00:01:59,900
No.

25
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:03,933
Hazel is serious.

26
00:02:04,467 --> 00:02:07,533
She truly believes
Coleen killed Jessica.

27
00:02:09,633 --> 00:02:12,733
Let her accuse
all she wants.

28
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,600
The truth will come out.

29
00:02:16,567 --> 00:02:18,667
Our child is innocent.

30
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:29,900
There.

31
00:02:37,633 --> 00:02:40,167
Why is it so grainy?

32
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:44,100
Those CCTV cameras
in the area are old.

33
00:02:44,867 --> 00:02:46,033
They are due for an upgrade.

34
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:53,267
I can't see Coleen
or Jessica clearly.

35
00:02:56,267 --> 00:02:57,367
Did you see that?

36
00:02:59,467 --> 00:03:00,667
It looks like I pushed her.

37
00:03:02,200 --> 00:03:04,467
It looks like I pushed Jessica.

38
00:03:05,733 --> 00:03:08,300
Dear, breathe. Calm down.

39
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:13,300
Coleen, the footage is low-res.
It's not clear at all.

40
00:03:13,433 --> 00:03:15,967
There's no proof
that you pushed her.

41
00:03:17,033 --> 00:03:20,867
But there's also no proof
that I didn't push her!

42
00:03:22,633 --> 00:03:27,000
Sweetie, no more negative
thoughts, all right?

43
00:03:27,733 --> 00:03:31,000
Joel, please rewind that part.

44
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:33,000
<i>The moment before
Jessica was hit.</i>

45
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:38,733
It's a black pickup. Looks new.

46
00:03:38,867 --> 00:03:41,800
Attorney, the image
is too blurry.

47
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,767
<i> We can't get the plate number.</i>

48
00:03:44,300 --> 00:03:49,033
Maybe we can check other cameras
from nearby intersections.

49
00:03:49,167 --> 00:03:51,267
Attorney, that's the bad news.

50
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,000
Every CCTV around the area
is broken.

51
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,100
What?

52
00:03:56,867 --> 00:04:00,133
How could they let that happen?
Why haven't they upgraded them?

53
00:04:00,867 --> 00:04:03,567
Let's reach out
to Colonel Sarabia.

54
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,233
The police are already
investigating, right?

55
00:04:06,367 --> 00:04:07,567
We can ask him for updates.

56
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,633
Or maybe he can help us himself.

57
00:04:09,767 --> 00:04:13,800
If the driver's car
has a dashcam,

58
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:15,733
he can see what really happened.

59
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,867
That Jessica wasn't pushed.

60
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,800
It was a hit-and-run, Joel.

61
00:04:23,933 --> 00:04:26,400
That's exactly what happened.
He ran from Coleen and Jessica.

62
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:35,867
<i>Why did you take Jessica
away from me so soon?</i>

63
00:04:36,533 --> 00:04:40,333
<i>You know what I went
through from losing Jeff,</i>

64
00:04:40,467 --> 00:04:42,100
<i> Andeng, and Coleen.</i>

65
00:04:43,633 --> 00:04:45,633
<i>Now that I finally have
them back in my life,</i>

66
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,500
<i> you took Jessica from me.</i>

67
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:50,400
<i> You're cruel.</i>

68
00:04:53,733 --> 00:04:56,467
Manuel, how are we
feeling today?

69
00:04:57,900 --> 00:05:00,100
- How are you doing?
- I'm all right, Doc.

70
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,867
Please check his IV.

71
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:05,067
All right, just a quick checkup.

72
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,067
Breathe in, breathe out, please.

73
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:10,367
I heard something.

74
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:13,200
They said what happened
at the wake wasn't good.

75
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:16,933
You and Hazel had an argument?

76
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:19,333
Yes, Doc.

77
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,667
It almost got physical.

78
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:27,067
No trauma? Were you hurt?

79
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:29,867
No, I wasn't hurt, Doc.

80
00:05:31,767 --> 00:05:33,867
Manuel, listen.

81
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,733
I only allowed you to go
to the wake

82
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:39,767
because I thought
your issues were settled.

83
00:05:40,367 --> 00:05:44,133
To be honest, you know how
delicate your condition is.

84
00:05:44,267 --> 00:05:46,600
You need to stay
completely stress-free.

85
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:49,033
Don't worry, Doc.
It won't happen again.

86
00:05:49,967 --> 00:05:52,233
Hazel and I won't be
seeing each other anyway.

87
00:05:53,233 --> 00:05:56,433
She forbade me from attending
our child's funeral.

88
00:05:58,067 --> 00:05:59,567
<i> Right.</i>

89
00:05:59,700 --> 00:06:01,733
Remember what we talked about?

90
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:03,400
About your leg?

91
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:07,800
I was able to speak
with Dr. Tamayo.

92
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:11,300
He's one of the top spine
surgery specialists here

93
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:13,033
in the Philippines.

94
00:06:13,167 --> 00:06:17,133
He's currently abroad,
but he emailed me.

95
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:19,200
He said he'll take your case.

96
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:20,600
So let's see.

97
00:06:20,733 --> 00:06:25,100
You might regain leg mobility
after some time.

98
00:06:25,233 --> 00:06:26,200
Is that okay?

99
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,367
Thank you, Doc.

100
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,200
Miss Felma, hi.

101
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,533
<i> Manuel is waiting for you.</i>

102
00:06:35,667 --> 00:06:36,833
Thank you, Doc.

103
00:06:51,867 --> 00:06:52,900
Manuel,

104
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:56,833
go to the funeral.

105
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:01,667
You have every right
to see Jessica.

106
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:06,000
You're her father.

107
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:09,733
Hazel will just
make a scene again.

108
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:15,100
And my daughter will
end up disrespected.

109
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:22,133
Felma, Jessica suffered
so much because of Hazel.

110
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:25,733
I just want her
to have peace,

111
00:07:28,167 --> 00:07:30,467
even if it's only
in her final moments.

112
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,733
Attorney, would you
like some dessert?

113
00:07:43,867 --> 00:07:47,500
There's some in the pantry.
Hilda hasn't brought it out yet.

114
00:07:47,667 --> 00:07:49,733
Yes, please.

115
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,267
She returned, Hazel.

116
00:07:56,733 --> 00:07:57,800
It's Felma.

117
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:00,667
Why?

118
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,833
What are you still doing here?

119
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:22,833
Didn't I kick you out earlier?

120
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:26,267
Isn't it clear
you're not welcome here?

121
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:30,667
Hazel, I'm only here
to ask one thing.

122
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:36,200
Please, let Manuel go
to Jessica's funeral.

123
00:08:38,933 --> 00:08:43,900
Give him a chance to say
goodbye to your daughter.

124
00:08:44,867 --> 00:08:45,633
No.

125
00:08:46,933 --> 00:08:48,833
He chose his illegitimate child.

126
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:51,767
He lost every right to mine.

127
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,767
Hazel, please.

128
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:58,600
Let him be here.

129
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,600
He's already broken inside.

130
00:09:02,867 --> 00:09:03,933
Have some mercy.

131
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:06,033
Mercy?

132
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,900
Did he ever have mercy on me?

133
00:09:10,967 --> 00:09:14,667
Did any of you even think
about the pain I went through...

134
00:09:16,067 --> 00:09:18,367
as a mother? None of you did.

135
00:09:19,467 --> 00:09:20,133
And you.

136
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:22,800
You stole my husband.

137
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:27,000
You took everything from me.

138
00:09:28,700 --> 00:09:30,433
Even Jessica's love.

139
00:09:31,900 --> 00:09:34,467
I lost my daughter
because of you.

140
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,900
I can't accept that.

141
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:38,833
You've taken everything,

142
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:42,100
even my right to be a mother.

143
00:09:44,567 --> 00:09:45,233
Fine.

144
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:52,633
Since you'll do anything
for my husband,

145
00:09:56,333 --> 00:09:57,600
I'll agree.

146
00:09:58,300 --> 00:10:03,800
He can go to the funeral
on one condition.

147
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:09,133
We won't go with him
if that's what you want.

148
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:10,333
No.

149
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:12,900
I want you to surrender Coleen.

150
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:20,500
Make her admit she's the reason
Jessica died.

151
00:10:20,633 --> 00:10:22,933
So that my daughter's death
will be given justice.

152
00:10:23,067 --> 00:10:24,567
That's my condition.

153
00:10:25,300 --> 00:10:26,300
What?

154
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:28,433
Wouldn't you do anything?

155
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,333
Aren't you that
desperate for Manuel?

156
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:36,100
That's my only condition.

157
00:10:36,600 --> 00:10:37,500
Nothing else.

158
00:10:39,567 --> 00:10:40,700
Hazel, no.

159
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:47,400
Coleen will never confess
to a crime you just made up.

160
00:10:48,333 --> 00:10:50,900
Then we have nothing
more to talk about.

161
00:10:52,233 --> 00:10:53,333
You can leave now.

162
00:11:16,533 --> 00:11:19,000
Are there any updates
about what happened to Jessica?

163
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:20,800
None so far.

164
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:24,400
Andrea, Jeff.
The attorney is here.

165
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:26,433
- Attorney.
- Hi, good afternoon.

166
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:27,367
- Attorney.
- Hi.

167
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,800
- Good afternoon.
- Hello, hello.

168
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:30,300
- Hello, hello.
- Attorney.

169
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:31,500
Please sit down.

170
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:32,533
Thank you, thank you.

171
00:11:32,667 --> 00:11:34,333
Didang. Please bring a glass
for Attorney.

172
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:35,867
Thank you.

173
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:40,767
So my legal team's been
working closely

174
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:43,900
with the police investigation,
and they may have a lead

175
00:11:44,067 --> 00:11:47,333
on the hit-and-run suspect
in Jessica's case.

176
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:48,500
They've found something?

177
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:52,733
They discovered an abandoned
vehicle in Fairview.

178
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,000
No plates, but the same model.

179
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,367
Thank you, Attorney.

180
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:00,300
It looks very similar
to the one caught on CCTV.

181
00:12:01,733 --> 00:12:02,900
Yeah, it does look
like the same car.

182
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:05,400
The footage was just blurry,
but it looks the same.

183
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:10,667
The police can't confirm yet,
but it seems to match the dent

184
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:17,700
on the bumper right where
Jessica was hit in the footage.

185
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:52,533
Good thing you're awake.

186
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:00,700
Where did you go last night?

187
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:04,967
You came back so upset.

188
00:13:08,667 --> 00:13:11,100
I ran into Dr. Richard.

189
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:16,100
He said your progress
is consistent.

190
00:13:16,233 --> 00:13:18,333
Your laboratory results
look good, too.

191
00:13:18,467 --> 00:13:22,767
If you stay stable until
tomorrow, you can be discharged.

192
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:25,933
Felma, you didn't answer me.

193
00:13:27,133 --> 00:13:28,467
Where did you go last night?

194
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:34,833
I went back to the wake.

195
00:13:37,367 --> 00:13:42,667
I asked Hazel to let you attend
the funeral peacefully.

196
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,033
Felma, why did you do that?

197
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:50,133
Because I can feel your pain.

198
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,400
But she refused.

199
00:13:55,433 --> 00:13:59,333
She'll only allow it
if I surrender Coleen

200
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:00,900
and make her confess.

201
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:02,500
What?

202
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,767
<i> I'm sorry, Manuel.</i>

203
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:12,667
<i>I want you to go to the funeral,
but I won't give up Coleen.</i>

204
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:15,300
<i> Our daughter is innocent.</i>

205
00:14:16,433 --> 00:14:19,067
If I have to turn myself in,

206
00:14:21,733 --> 00:14:23,567
I'll do so.

207
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,133
For dad's sake.

208
00:14:35,567 --> 00:14:36,833
Coleen, sweetheart...

209
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:39,067
My child.

210
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:43,600
Why would you do that?

211
00:14:43,733 --> 00:14:45,700
You didn't do anything wrong.

212
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:52,267
I just want dad to see Jessica
one last time, Mom.

213
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:54,400
No, Coleen.

214
00:14:57,933 --> 00:14:58,800
Manuel,

215
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:01,833
I'm sorry.

216
00:15:04,133 --> 00:15:06,133
I want you to go to the funeral,

217
00:15:07,667 --> 00:15:12,667
but I won't agree
to Hazel's condition.

218
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:15,367
Coleen.

219
00:15:15,767 --> 00:15:17,200
Come here, sweetheart.

220
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:26,633
Is it true that
you pushed Jessica?

221
00:15:27,967 --> 00:15:29,600
Dad, no.

222
00:15:30,867 --> 00:15:34,600
We fought, yes,
but I didn't push her.

223
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:39,467
That's what I'm saying.
Then why surrender yourself?

224
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,367
For me?

225
00:15:44,233 --> 00:15:48,200
So you'd lie? Take the blame
for something you didn't do?

226
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:53,067
Just so I can go
to your sister's funeral?

227
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:57,567
Dad, I just want you
to be happy.

228
00:15:58,767 --> 00:16:00,767
I know, sweetheart.

229
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:06,000
But it's not right to sacrifice
yourself for someone you love.

230
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:08,200
Dad,

231
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:12,300
please don't be mad at me.

232
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:16,100
I couldn't save Jessica.

233
00:16:18,833 --> 00:16:20,533
Dad, I'm sorry.

234
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:26,633
I'm sorry you can't go
to her funeral because of me.

235
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:31,667
I'm so sorry, Dad...

236
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:36,133
Dad, I'm sorry.

237
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:39,800
I'm sorry, Dad.

238
00:17:00,033 --> 00:17:01,100
Friend,

239
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:04,967
are you really not going to let
Manuel attend the funeral?

240
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:09,200
No.

241
00:17:10,967 --> 00:17:12,733
They refuse to surrender Coleen.

242
00:17:13,667 --> 00:17:19,367
But, Hazel, you have no proof of
your accusations against Coleen.

243
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:23,733
This might all backfire on you.
You wouldn't want that.

244
00:17:23,867 --> 00:17:25,833
Am I right, Attorney?

245
00:17:25,967 --> 00:17:26,767
<i> Yes.</i>

246
00:17:27,867 --> 00:17:31,433
Mrs. Cruz, they can sue you
for slander,

247
00:17:31,933 --> 00:17:35,433
unjust vexation,
and psychological abuse.

248
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:42,267
That's why I'm advising you
to stop accusing Coleen,

249
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:44,167
<i> especially in public.</i>

250
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:47,533
Any news from the police
investigation, Attorney?

251
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:51,933
Actually, yes.

252
00:17:53,467 --> 00:17:56,767
They've found an abandoned
pickup truck.

253
00:17:57,567 --> 00:18:01,800
And they suspect it's the one
that hit Jessica.

254
00:18:02,667 --> 00:18:04,900
But we have no
confirmation yet.

255
00:18:05,933 --> 00:18:07,300
I hope they catch whoever
did this

256
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,767
to give justice
for my goddaughter.

257
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:15,567
Jessica's death will only
be given justice

258
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:18,200
when Coleen is already
behind bars.

259
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:20,000
- Hazel...
- Hazel...

260
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,300
No matter what you say,

261
00:18:24,667 --> 00:18:26,300
she pushed Jessica.

262
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,367
That's why my daughter was hit.

263
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:33,333
Coleen still killed Jessica.

264
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:52,767
Sweetheart...

265
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,767
This is the last time
I'll be with you.

266
00:19:00,833 --> 00:19:02,100
The worst part is,

267
00:19:04,333 --> 00:19:06,300
I didn't even get
to see your face.

268
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,133
It was ruined
because of Coleen.

269
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:13,567
That's why I promise you, dear.

270
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:16,733
I will not let Coleen
have some peace.

271
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:21,367
Even if I can't ruin
their faces,

272
00:19:22,733 --> 00:19:23,767
I promise...

273
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,733
I will destroy their family.

274
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,367
I have no words.

275
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,933
I never thought...

276
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:57,033
this day would come.

277
00:20:00,567 --> 00:20:02,033
I'll bury you...

278
00:20:03,267 --> 00:20:04,667
while I'm still alive.

279
00:20:10,767 --> 00:20:15,733
No, it shouldn't be me
burying you.

280
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:20,367
You should be burying me, dear.

281
00:20:26,967 --> 00:20:28,033
Thank you.

282
00:20:29,233 --> 00:20:30,700
Thank you.

283
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,067
Even for a moment,

284
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:39,967
you made me feel I was a mother.

285
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:42,333
But now...

286
00:20:44,633 --> 00:20:46,000
now that you're gone...

287
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,667
Who am I even striving for?

288
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:53,067
Who am I even living for?

289
00:20:57,567 --> 00:20:59,133
I wasn't a perfect mom.

290
00:21:02,333 --> 00:21:04,400
I hurt you so many times.

291
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:06,733
I'm sorry.

292
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:09,900
Sorry, Jessica.

293
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:14,667
I hope you knew how much
I loved you.

294
00:21:15,900 --> 00:21:17,433
<i> No matter what happened,</i>

295
00:21:19,467 --> 00:21:20,767
<i> you were my child.</i>

296
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,700
My flesh and blood.

297
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,300
You came from me.

298
00:21:27,067 --> 00:21:28,267
You were mine.

299
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:32,000
<i> I failed you in so many ways.</i>

300
00:21:35,633 --> 00:21:37,233
<i>Dear, I want to make it up
to you.</i>

301
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,200
<i> But how?</i>

302
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:45,500
It's too late.

303
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,200
It's all too late, dear.

304
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:50,667
Everything is too late.

305
00:21:52,567 --> 00:21:53,600
<i> Forgive me.</i>

306
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:57,867
Jessica, forgive me, my child.

307
00:21:58,800 --> 00:21:59,867
Jessica...

308
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:01,767
my child.

309
00:22:03,433 --> 00:22:04,967
Dear...

310
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,500
I'm sorry.

311
00:22:07,933 --> 00:22:09,267
Forgive...

312
00:22:09,967 --> 00:22:11,700
<i> Forgive me.</i>

313
00:22:11,833 --> 00:22:14,800
Dear, I'm sorry.

314
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:16,900
<i>Sorry, I wasn't able
to do anything.</i>

315
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:19,500
Sorry, sorry...

316
00:23:15,167 --> 00:23:19,133
<i>We're very sorry for all
the trouble we've caused.</i>

317
00:23:19,267 --> 00:23:23,267
<i>I'm the product
of my parents' mistake.</i>

318
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:27,267
<i>And yet, you were
so kind to me.</i>

319
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,267
<i> Thank you so much.</i>

320
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:03,467
You monsters!

321
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:05,633
The audacity!

322
00:24:19,067 --> 00:24:22,333
It's so hard to accept
that your sister is really gone.

323
00:24:23,067 --> 00:24:25,267
I wish you had
more time together.

324
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:26,900
Dad, I'm right here.

325
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,700
I won't leave you.

326
00:24:29,133 --> 00:24:31,333
Friend, what's your plan?

327
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:32,900
I'm moving houses, too.

328
00:24:33,033 --> 00:24:35,267
Just preparing
for Manuel's return.

329
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:37,733
Just wait and see, Alice.

330
00:24:39,467 --> 00:24:41,333
You're shameless, Coleen.

331
00:24:41,467 --> 00:24:44,233
You actually had
the nerve to come here.

332
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:46,567
Are we leaving now?

333
00:24:46,700 --> 00:24:48,700
We just got here.

334
00:24:49,233 --> 00:24:51,233
Mrs. Cruz!
